In a corporate setting with users authenticating through an AD it is desirable to have the email attribute kept current by updating it from the AD whenever the user logs in. 

However, there may be cases when this attribute is missing from the user's AD object. In such cases the email address is currently removed from the confluence user object. While the email address is an optional attributes where AD user objects are concerned, it is a required attribute for Jira users.

Please amend the code or add a switch that will only update the email address of a Jira user if the contributing source attribute is non-empty.

